            problem: "The game lacked player identity and self-expression — everything was functional, nothing was personal. Players had no way to show personality, achievement, or taste within the game world. The design challenge: introduce meaningful customization that enhances rather than distracts from core gameplay, while creating sustainable value for both players and the game economy.",
            approach: "**Design Philosophy**: Cosmetics should amplify gameplay satisfaction, not replace it — beauty serves function.\n\n1. **Identity Through Play**: Tile customization directly enhances the core word-formation experience, making every game feel more personal without changing mechanics.\n2. **Acquisition Psychology**: Gacha mechanics balanced through Machinations modeling to create anticipation and satisfaction while avoiding predatory patterns.\n3. **Ecosystem Integration**: Cosmetics woven into existing progression systems (Food Fiesta rewards) rather than isolated, ensuring coherent player journey.\n4. **Collection Design**: Rarity tiers create natural aspiration ladders — common tiles for immediate satisfaction, rare tiles for long-term goals, maintaining engagement across player commitment levels.",
